{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rerun-io/rerun/pulls/11513", "id": 2910404702, "node_id": "PR_kwDOHJFhi86teUBe", "html_url": "https://github.com/rerun-io/rerun/pull/11513", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rerun-io/rerun/pull/11513.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rerun-io/rerun/pull/11513.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rerun-io/rerun/issues/11513", "number": 11513, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Flatten connection_client error hierarchy", "user": {"login": "andrea-reale", "id": 154321632, "node_id": "U_kgDOCTLC4A", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/154321632?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale", "html_url": "https://github.com/andrea-reale", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/andrea-reale/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "### Related\r\n\r\n- Part of RR-2395\r\n\r\n### Why\r\nWhen it comes to exposing errors to client (and specifically thinking at the Python SDK) we want:\r\n- To have meaningful error messages that humans (primarily users and secondarily developers) can understand\r\n- To have actionable types that computers can use to react to errors\r\n\r\nOur previous taxonomy of errors in the client was very deeply nested and made it hard to classify the errors\r\nin a way that was machine friendly, i.e., it was hiding very deep the underlying source of the error, and mainly\r\nhighlighting the operation where the error happened.\r\n\r\n### What\r\n\r\nThis is an attempt to flatten that taxonomy. All errors generated by the connection client will be of type `ApiError` and \r\nwill have a `ApiErrorKind` of one of few types. The assumption is that those  types are generic across all operations,\r\nand are machine actionable.\r\n\r\n`ApiError` is expected to include a human understandable error message string as well as wrapping the underlying `source`\r\nof the error, for further inspection.\r\n\r\n### Next\r\nIn my ideal mental world, `ExternalError` in `rerun_py` should follow a similar model (or even disappear completely in favor of a more global `ApiError`-equivalent). This will allow to have all the possible error in just a bunch of useful classes instead of this odd mixed taxonomy.\r\n\r\nI did not do it in this PR because I would have had too touch way more things I am willing to at this stage.\r\n\r\n\r\n", "created_at": "2025-10-13T14:13:13Z", "updated_at": "2025-10-14T11:57:03Z", "closed_at": "2025-10-14T11:57:01Z", "merged_at": "2025-10-14T11:57:01Z", "merge_commit_sha": "f6cf62debc859cf78d645319306583bca63b28e3", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [{"id": 5833649472, "node_id": "LA_kwDOHJFhi88AAAABW7ZtQA", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rerun-io/rerun/labels/exclude%20from%20changelog", "name": "exclude from changelog", "color": "ACC116", "default": false, "description": "PRs with this won't show up in CHANGELOG.md"}, {"id": 7681994473, "node_id": "LA_kwDOHJFhi88AAAAByeHu6Q", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rerun-io/rerun/labels/dataplatform", "name": "dataplatform", "color": "d4c5f9", "default": false, "description": "Rerun Data Platform integration"}], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rerun-io/rerun/pulls/11513/commits",